{"type": "user", "message": {"role": "user", "content": [{"tool_use_id": "chatcmpl-tool-b23dfabcf4e8cbb4", "type": "tool_result", "content": "Paper 2607.03985 not found\n===\n# CosyVoice 2: Scalable Streaming Speech Synthesis with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2412.10117\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Yuxuan Wang, Qian Chen, Xian Shi, Xiang Lv, Tianyu Zhao, Zhifu Gao, Yexin Yang, Changfeng Gao, Hui Wang, Fan Yu, Huadai Liu, Zhengyan Sheng, Yue Gu, Chong Deng, Wen Wang, Shiliang Zhang, Zhijie Yan, Jingren Zhou\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introducing CosyVoice 2, a scalable streaming speech synthesis model that integrates large language models with a speech decoder.\n  2. Designing a unified architecture that seamlessly supports both streaming and non-streaming speech synthesis.\n  3. Developing a large language model equipped with block-wise causal attention to effectively balance lookahead context and streaming latency.\n  4. Implementing a modified finite scalar quantization strategy with an adaptive weight to achieve high-compression and high-accuracy speech tokenization.\n  5. Demonstrating through comprehensive experiments that the proposed model significantly outperforms its predecessor and achieves state-of-the-art performance in speech synthesis.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-流式, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# NaturalSpeech 3: Zero-Shot Speech Synthesis with Factorized Codec and Diffusion Models\narXiv: 2403.03100\nAuthors: Zeqian Ju, Yuancheng Wang, Kai Shen, Xu Tan, Detai Xin, Dongchao Yang, Yanqing Liu, Yichong Leng, Kaitao Song, Siliang Tang, Zhizheng Wu, Tao Qin, Xiang-Yang Li, Wei Ye, Shikun Zhang, Jiang Bian, Lei He, Jinyu Li, Sheng Zhao\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A novel neural speech codec with factorized vector quantization is proposed to disentangle speech waveforms into distinct subspaces of content, prosody, timbre, and acoustic details.\n  2. A factorized diffusion model is introduced to generate speech attributes in each disentangled subspace following their corresponding prompts in a divide-and-conquer manner.\n  3. The system achieves state-of-the-art performance and human-level naturalness on the multi-speaker LibriSpeech dataset for zero-shot text-to-speech synthesis.\n  4. The factorization design enables flexible speech attribute manipulation by allowing different prompts to control different attributes independently.\n  5. The effectiveness of the system is further improved by scaling the model to 1 billion parameters and the training data to 200K hours.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-参考语音, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "is_error": false}]}, "parent_tool_use_id": null, "session_id": "63ccb5d0-c086-4578-b7db-f621cc76b322", "uuid": "ffff300a-c51a-44d5-bf5c-89e9c2918c6b", "timestamp": "2026-07-07T09:30:54.119Z", "tool_use_result": {"stdout": "Paper 2607.03985 not found\n===\n# CosyVoice 2: Scalable Streaming Speech Synthesis with Large Language Models\narXiv: 2412.10117\nAuthors: Zhihao Du, Yuxuan Wang, Qian Chen, Xian Shi, Xiang Lv, Tianyu Zhao, Zhifu Gao, Yexin Yang, Changfeng Gao, Hui Wang, Fan Yu, Huadai Liu, Zhengyan Sheng, Yue Gu, Chong Deng, Wen Wang, Shiliang Zhang, Zhijie Yan, Jingren Zhou\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: \nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. Introducing CosyVoice 2, a scalable streaming speech synthesis model that integrates large language models with a speech decoder.\n  2. Designing a unified architecture that seamlessly supports both streaming and non-streaming speech synthesis.\n  3. Developing a large language model equipped with block-wise causal attention to effectively balance lookahead context and streaming latency.\n  4. Implementing a modified finite scalar quantization strategy with an adaptive weight to achieve high-compression and high-accuracy speech tokenization.\n  5. Demonstrating through comprehensive experiments that the proposed model significantly outperforms its predecessor and achieves state-of-the-art performance in speech synthesis.\n\nTags: TTS, TTS/架构-AR-LLM, TTS/功能-流式, TTS/功能-多语言, TTS/控制-参考语音\n===\n# NaturalSpeech 3: Zero-Shot Speech Synthesis with Factorized Codec and Diffusion Models\narXiv: 2403.03100\nAuthors: Zeqian Ju, Yuancheng Wang, Kai Shen, Xu Tan, Detai Xin, Dongchao Yang, Yanqing Liu, Yichong Leng, Kaitao Song, Siliang Tang, Zhizheng Wu, Tao Qin, Xiang-Yang Li, Wei Ye, Shikun Zhang, Jiang Bian, Lei He, Jinyu Li, Sheng Zhao\nYear: 2024 | Venue: \nTopic: tts_vc\nStatus: unread\n\nContributions:\n  1. A novel neural speech codec with factorized vector quantization is proposed to disentangle speech waveforms into distinct subspaces of content, prosody, timbre, and acoustic details.\n  2. A factorized diffusion model is introduced to generate speech attributes in each disentangled subspace following their corresponding prompts in a divide-and-conquer manner.\n  3. The system achieves state-of-the-art performance and human-level naturalness on the multi-speaker LibriSpeech dataset for zero-shot text-to-speech synthesis.\n  4. The factorization design enables flexible speech attribute manipulation by allowing different prompts to control different attributes independently.\n  5. The effectiveness of the system is further improved by scaling the model to 1 billion parameters and the training data to 200K hours.\n\nTags: TTS, 压缩, TTS/架构-NAR-Diffusion, TTS/控制-参考语音, 压缩/量化-VQ, 压缩/语义声学-语义, 压缩/语义声学-声学, 压缩/语义声学-混合", "stderr": "", "interrupted": false, "isImage": false, "noOutputExpected": false}}
